Rule: Git Checkpointing (flofile_clean)

Instruction:
When I say "git checkpoint this":

1. Run these commands:
git pull --ff-only
git add -A
git commit -m "Checkpoint: $(date +"%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S")" --allow-empty
git push origin main

2. Always commit & push to the repo:
https://github.com/mblinch/flofile_clean.git
on branch main.

3. Never create or push to rescue/today. If I’m not on main, stop and ask me.

4. After running, show me:
- The branch
- The latest commit hash and message
- Confirmation it’s pushed to GitHub

---

Rule: No Silent Reverts

Instruction:
Never run git reset, git rebase, git checkout, or any command that would move the project to an older commit, branch, or state unless I explicitly ask for it.

If you think a revert, rebase, or reset might be needed, stop and ask me first.

Always confirm with me before executing any command that could discard, overwrite, or roll back work.